Lone Tree Wind, LLC PUBLIC VERSION Exhibit No. LT-14 CUI//CEII INFORMATION HAS BEEN REMOVED Execution Version SHARED FACILITIES AGREEMENT THIS SHARED FACILITIES AGREEMENT (this Agreement), dated as of August 26, 2020 (the Effective Date), is made and entered into by and between CRESCENT RIDGE LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (Crescent Ridge and, in its capacity as manager of the Shared Facilities under this Agreement, the Shared Facilities Manager) and LONE TREE WIND, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (Lone Tree Wind) (together, the Parties and each, a Party). RECITALS WHEREAS, Crescent Ridge is a party, as Interconnection Customer thereunder, to that certain Third Revised Interconnection Service Agreement No. 3831 made and entered into as of July 31, 2015 (as it may be amended from time to time, the Crescent Ridge ISA), by and among Crescent Ridge, the PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. (PJM or Transmission Provider) and Commonwealth Edison Company (Transmission Owner), relating to a 54.45 MW electric generating facility (the Crescent Ridge Project); and WHEREAS, the Crescent Ridge ISA states that the Crescent Ridge Wind Farm has a Maximum Facility Output (as defined therein) of 54.45 MW and Capacity Interconnection Rights (as defined therein) of 9.7 MW; and WHEREAS, Lone Tree Wind is a party, as Interconnection Customer thereunder, to that certain Interconnection Service Agreement No. 5594 made and entered into as of April 20, 2020 (as it may be amended from time to time, the Lone Tree Wind ISA and together with the Crescent Ridge ISA, the Interconnection Agreements), by and among Lone Tree Wind, PJM and Transmission Owner, relating to a 79.4 MW electric generating facility(the Lone Tree Wind Project); and WHEREAS, the Lone Tree Wind ISA states that the Lone Tree Wind Project has a net maximum summer/winter energy output of 79.4 MW and Capacity Interconnection Rights (as defined therein) of 19 MW; and WHEREAS, Schedule B of both the Crescent Ridge ISA and the Lone Tree Wind ISA identify the same location as the Point of Interconnection (as defined therein) for each Project; and WHEREAS, the Crescent Ridge Project owns and intends to share with the Lone Tree Wind Project the use of certain premises (the Shared Premises), pursuant to and as more specifically described in that certain Shared Facilities Easement and Lease dated on or about the date hereof, and may be referred to herein as Co-Tenants; and WHEREAS, Crescent Ridge owns and has procured, installed, and constructed certain electrical and communications facilities, including a 138 kV substation and related infrastructure and equipment that are necessary, in part to interconnect each of the Lone Tree Wind Project and the Crescent Ridge Project to the transmission grid at the Point of Interconnection as identified in Exhibit A (the Shared Facilities); and 1 Execution Version WHEREAS, Crescent Ridge desires to convey an Undivided Interest in such Shared Facilities to Lone Tree Wind such that the Crescent Ridge Project and the Lone Tree Wind Project can share use of the Shared Facilities pursuant to this Agreement; and WHEREAS, Lone Tree Wind will own and construct certain electrical equipment upgrades to the interconnection facilities of the Crescent Ridge Project and the Lone Tree Wind Project at the Point of Interconnection identified in Exhibit A; and WHEREAS, Lone Tree Wind and Crescent Ridge agree that Crescent Ridge shall be the Shared Facilities Manager to provide day-to-day, routine operation and maintenance services to Lone Tree Wind and Crescent Ridge for the Shared Premises and Shared Facilities and the Shared Facilities Manager desires to provide such services for Lone Tree Wind and Crescent Ridge in accordance with the terms hereof; and WHEREAS, the Parties are not agreeing to provide any Federal Energy Regulatory Commission (FERC)-jurisdictional interconnection or transmission service to each other pursuant to this Agreement and rather shall receive such services as they may be provided from the Transmission Owner and/or Transmission Provider through the Shared Facilities pursuant to the Crescent Ridge ISA or the Lone Tree Wind ISA, as appropriate; AGREEMENT NOW, THEREFORE, in consideration of the foregoing and of the mutual covenants and agreements contained herein, and for other good and valuable consideration, the receipt and sufficiency of which is hereby acknowledged, each of the Parties hereby agrees as follows: ARTICLE I DEFINITIONS The following capitalized terms will have the respective meanings set forth below: Affiliate of a Person means a Person that directly or indirectly through one or more intermediaries, controls, or is controlled by, or is under common control with, such Person. As used in this definition, control (including, with its correlative meanings, controlled by and under common control with) shall mean possession, directly or indirectly, of power to direct or cause the direction of management or policies (whether through ownership of securities or partnership or other ownership interests, by contract or otherwise). Agreement means this Shared Facilities Agreement, as amended from time to time. Approved Credit Support means credit support acceptable to the Shared Facilities Manager for the ongoing payment obligations under this Agreement, the Crescent Ridge ISA, and the Lone Tree Wind ISA. Approved Shared Facilities O&M Budget has the meaning set forth in Section 6.9(a). 2 Execution Version Bankruptcy Event means, with respect to any Party, such Party: (a) voluntarily files a petition or otherwise commences, authorizes or acquiesces in the commencement of a proceeding or cause of action under any bankruptcy, insolvency, reorganization or similar law, or has any such petition filed or commenced against it by its creditors and such petition is not dismissed within sixty (60) days of the filing or commencement or an order for relief is entered; (b) makes an assignment or any general arrangement for the benefit of creditors; (c) otherwise becomes insolvent, however evidenced; (d) has a liquidator, administrator, receiver, trustee, conservator or similar official appointed with respect to it or any substantial portion of its property or assets; or (e) is generally unable to pay its debts as they fall due. Confidential Information has the meaning set forth in Section 11.4. Construction Start Date means, for any Project, the date on which commencement of on-site construction of (a) roads and (b) the initial wind turbine foundation for the Project have occurred. Co-Tenant has the meaning set forth in the Recitals. Crescent Ridge has the meaning set forth in the Preamble. Crescent Ridge ISA has the meaning set forth in the Recitals. Crescent Ridge Project has the meaning set forth in the Recitals. Default Rate shall mean the lesser of (i) the Prime Rate plus three percent (3%) per annum, or (ii) the maximum rate allowed by law. Demand has the meaning set forth in Section 7.4. Demanding Party has the meaning set forth in Section 7.4. Disclosing Party has the meaning set forth in Section 11.4. Effective Date has the meaning set forth in the Preamble. Emergency shall mean any occurrence, in the reasonable judgment of a Co- Tenant or the Shared Facilities Manager, that may arise that requires immediate action and (i) which constitutes a serious actual or potential hazard to the safety of persons or property, or (ii) may materially interfere with the safe, reliable, economical or environmentally sound operation of the Shared Premises and Shared Facilities. Event of Default has the meaning set forth in Section 9.1. FERC means the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission and any successor agency. Force Majeure means acts of God or any other casualty or occurrence, condition, event or circumstance of any kind or nature not reasonably within the affected Party's control and 3 Execution Version which could not have been avoided by reasonable measures by the affected Party, including strikes, slow-downs or labor difficulties, fires, flood, earthquakes, explosions, natural disasters, or other hazards, equipment failure where such equipment has been maintained in accordance with Prudent Industry Practices, acts of public enemies, riots, civil commotions, insurrection, or war. Force Majeure expressly does not include: any delay in performing or failure of performance of any contractual provision by a Party (except to the extent caused by a Force Majeure event); late delivery or breakage of equipment or materials ( except to the extent caused by a Force Majeure event); or economic hardship. GDPIPD shall mean the implicit price deflator for the gross domestic product as computed and published by the U.S. Department of Commerce. The figures to be used in this adjustment shall be those presented in the Gross Domestic Product: Third Quarter Final Press Release typically released in December of each calendar year by the United States Department of Commerce, Bureau of Economic Analysis. No subsequent revisions released by the United States Department of Commerce to those figures will be considered to affect or adjust the Inflation Adjustment Factor. Governmental Authority means any federal, state, local or other governmental, judicial, public or statutory instrumentality, tribunal, agency, authority, body or entity, or any political subdivision thereof or any regional transmission authority, having legal jurisdiction over the matter or person in question, and specifically includes the North American Electric Reliability Corporation (NERC) and regional electric reliability councils. Indemnified Party has the meaning set forth in Section 4.1. Indemnifying Party has the meaning set forth in Section 4.1. Inflation Adjustment Factor shall mean a fraction, the numerator of which is the GDPIPD for the prior calendar year and the denominator of which is the GDPIPD for the next prior calendar year; provided that such fraction shall be converted to decimal format to be carried to five (5) decimal places. Interconnection Agreements has the meaning set forth in the Recitals. Laws means all applicable laws, statutes, ordinances, rules, regulations, decrees, policies, orders, permits, requirements, judgments, decisions, injunctions and findings of or issued by any Governmental Authority, including laws relating to health, safety and the environment. Lone Tree Wind has the meaning set forth in the Preamble. Lone Tree Wind ISA has the meaning set forth in the Recitals. Lone Tree Wind Project has the meaning set forth in the Recitals. Losses has the meaning set forth in Section 4.1. Non-Pledging Party has the meaning set forth in Section 8.3(iv). 4 Execution Version Party or Parties has the meaning set forth in the Preamble. Person means any individual, partnership, joint venture, company, corporation, limited liability company, limited duration company, limited life company, association, trust or other entity or organization, including a government or political subdivision or an agency or instrumentality thereof. Pledging Party has the meaning set forth in Section 8.3(iv). Point of Interconnection has the meaning set forth in the Recitals. Prime Rate means the rate of interest per annum publicly announced from time to time by JPMorgan Chase & Co. as its prime lending rate in effect at its principal office in New York City, provided, however, that if such prime lending rate is no longer publicly announced by JPMorgan Chase & Co., Prime Rate shall mean the rate of interest published from time to time in The Wall Street Journal or its successor publication as its prime lending rate in effect. Project means the electric generating and associated equipment and facilities of the Crescent Ridge Project and/or the Lone Tree Wind Project. Project Controlled Assets means, for each Project, the land and facilities that are part of the Project but are not Shared Premises or Shared Facilities. Pro Rata Share means, for each Co-Tenant, the percentage interest of such Co- Tenant in the Shared Facilities, as set forth in Section 2.1(a) and as may be updated pursuant to Section 2.1(c). Prudent Industry Practices shall mean those practices, methods and acts that would be implemented and followed by a prudent operator of wind generating facilities similar to the Projects in the United States during the relevant time period, which practices, methods and acts, in the exercise of prudent and responsible professional judgment in the light of the facts known at the time the decision was made, could reasonably have been expected to accomplish the desired result consistent with good business practices, reliability and safety. In determining which practices, methods and acts constitute Prudent Industry Practices, due regard shall be given to, among other things, manufacturers warranties, contractual obligations, the requirements or guidance of Governmental Authorities and the Transmission Provider, applicable Laws, and the requirements of insurers, but in no event shall Prudent Industry Practices be interpreted to require any practice, method or act that violates applicable Laws. Recipient Party has the meaning set forth in Section 11.4. Related Parties shall mean, in the case of any Person, the partners, members, managers, officers, directors, employees, contractors, attorneys, financial advisors, agents and other advisors or representatives of such Person. Repowering means the planned major maintenance and partial refurbishment of the Crescent Ridge Project that includes the installation of new turbines and related equipment in order to improve the operational efficiency of the Crescent Ridge Project. 5 Execution Version Repowering COD has the meaning set forth in Section 2.1(c). Repowering Notice means a written notice in which Crescent Ridge confirms, as of the date specified in such notice, (i) that it has elected to proceed with the Repowering, (ii) the elected nameplate capacity for the repowered Crescent Ridge Project, (iii) notice to proceed (or the substantial equivalent thereof) has been issued with respect to the Repowering, and (iv) all costs and expenses associated with interconnecting the repowered Crescent Ridge Project into the Shared Facilities and any proposed improvements to the Shared Facilities. Rules has the meaning set forth in Section 7.3. Secured Party shall mean, with respect to a Co-Tenant, (i) the agent or lead bank or lending institution under a loan agreement with a Party or other entity secured by any of the Shared Premises and Facilities, or all or a portion of such Co-Tenants Undivided Interest, (ii) the owner lessor or other entity acquiring a Project or undivided ownership interest therein pursuant to a lease financing, (iii) any other entity providing financing for a Project, including through tax equity financing, (iv) any other party acknowledged by such Co-Tenant as a Secured Party in writing; provided, however, that no party shall be deemed a Secured Party entitled to the rights accruing to a Secured Party until such party gives written notice to each of the Co-Tenants along with an address for receipt of notices. Shared Expenses has the meaning set forth in Section 6.1. Shared Facilities has the meaning set forth in the Recitals. Shared Facilities Manager means the Person appointed manager of the Shared Facilities, which Person shall perform the obligations of Shared Facilities Manager as set forth in this Agreement and which Person shall be appointed, removed and replaced in accordance with Section 5.2 of this Agreement. The initial Shared Facilities Manager shall be Crescent Ridge. Shared Facilities Manager Fee has the meaning set forth in Section 6.1. Shared Facilities O&M Budget has the meaning set forth in Section 6.9(a). Shared Facilities Operating Manual has the meaning set forth in Section 5.5(d). Shared Premises has the meaning set forth in the Recitals. Shared Premises and Facilities means the Shared Premises and Shared Facilities, collectively. Surrendering Party has the meaning set forth in Section 2.4. Term has the meaning set forth in ARTICLE III. Transfer means to sell, transfer, assign, set over, deliver, convey, dispose of or otherwise demise an interest in tangible assets or intangible property, including this Agreement. 6 Execution Version Transmission Owner has the meaning set forth in the Recitals and any successor thereto. Transmission Provider has the meaning set forth in the Recitals and any successor thereto. Undivided Interest means, for each Co-Tenant, such Co-Tenants undivided interest as tenant in common in all rights, title and interest in and to the Shared Facilities. ARTICLE II CONVEYANCE AND UNDIVIDED INTEREST 2.1 Transfer of Shared Facilities. (a) Pursuant to the terms of this Agreement, Crescent Ridge hereby agrees to Transfer to Lone Tree Wind an Undivided Interest, as a tenant in common with Crescent Ridge, in and to the Shared Facilities in an amount equal to 59.3% of the Shared Facilities, resulting in Crescent Ridge retaining an Undivided Interest, as a tenant in common with Lone Tree Wind, in and to the Shared Facilities in an amount equal to 40.7% of the Shared Facilities. (b) Concurrently with the execution and delivery of this Agreement, Crescent Ridge and Lone Tree Wind will execute and deliver a Bill of Sale, substantially in the form attached hereto as Exhibit C (Bill of Sale), pursuant to which Crescent Ridge and Lone Tree Wind will consummate the Transfers described above. Upon the Effective Date and execution and delivery of the Bill of Sale, the Transfers will vest in Crescent Ridge and Lone Tree Wind ownership in the Shared Facilities in the amount of their respective Undivided Interests. (c) Crescent Ridge shall deliver the Repowering Notice to Lone Tree Wind upon the issuance of the notice to proceed (or the substantial equivalent thereof) with respect to the Repowering. Crescent Ridge shall further notify Lone Tree Wind in writing on or before the commercial operation date of the repowered Crescent Ridge Project (the Repowering COD). No later than five (5) days following the Repowering COD, (i) the Co-Tenants shall unwind the initial Transfer of Undivided Interests in the Shared Facilities made pursuant to Section 2.1(a) above and (ii) simultaneously with the unwinding of the initial exchange of Undivided Interests, Crescent Ridge will Transfer to Lone Tree Wind an Undivided Interest, as tenant in common with Crescent Ridge, in and to the Shared Facilities in an amount sufficient for Lone Tree Winds transmission of electricity generated from the Lone Tree Wind Project to the Point of Interconnection, by executing and delivering a bill of sale for the new Undivided Interest to Lone Tree Wind. Crescent Ridge shall pay Lone Tree Winds actual, out-of-pocket costs and expenses incurred in connection with the foregoing unwind and reconveyance of Undivided Interests or the Repowering. (d) At all times during the Term, (i) Lone Tree Winds Undivided Interests shall be sufficient for Lone Tree Winds transmission of electricity generated from the Lone Tree Wind Project to the Point of Interconnection and (ii) Crescent Ridges Undivided Interests shall be sufficient for Crescent Ridges transmission of electricity generated from the Crescent Ridge Project to the Point of Interconnection. 2.2 Shared Premises. 7 Execution Version The Parties shall reasonably cooperate with each other in connection with their respective uses of the Shared Premises, and each Party shall use commercially reasonable efforts to limit any interference with the other Partys use and enjoyment of the Shared Premises. 2.3 Conveyance; Condition of Property. EXCEPT AS OTHERWISE SET FORTH HEREIN, ALL CONVEYANCES AND TRANSFERS OF THE SHARED FACILITIES MADE PURSUANT TO THIS AGREEMENT ARE MADE AS IS, WITH ALL FAULTS AND WITHOUT WARRANTY, EITHER EXPRESS OR IMPLIED, INCLUDING, WITHOUT LIMITATION, ANY WARRANTIES OF QUALITY, MERCHANTABILITY, SUITABILITY AND FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE, ANY WARRANTIES REGARDING THE EXISTENCE OF ANY SECURITY INTEREST, LIEN OR ENCUMBRANCE, AND ANY WARRANTIES ARISING BY COMMON LAW, EXCEPT THAT (A) EACH PARTY REPRESENTS AND WARRANTS THAT IT HAS GOOD AND MARKETABLE VALID TITLE TO THE SHARED FACILITIES AND THAT IT IS GRANTING AN INTEREST IN SUCH SHARED FACILITIES UNDER THIS AGREEMENT FREE AND CLEAR OF ALL LIENS, CLAIMS AND ENCUMBRANCES AND (B) EACH PARTY REPRESENTS AND WARRANTS THAT IT HAS THE FULL POWER, RIGHT, AND AUTHORITY TO CONVEY ANY SHARED FACILITIES CONVEYED HEREUNDER. 2.4 Surrender and Assignment. A Co-Tenant who abandons or decommissions its Project shall convey its Undivided Interest and assign its rights hereunder to the other Co-Tenant at no cost or expense to the other Co-Tenant and, thereupon, cease to have any right, title or interest in its Undivided Interest (such Co-Tenant, a Surrendering Party). The Surrendering Party must (a) deliver all instruments of transfer as may be necessary or appropriate to effect the conveyance of its Undivided Interest and assignment of its rights hereunder to, and which are reasonably satisfactory to, the remaining Party; (b) assign and convey to the remaining Co-Tenant all its rights under this Agreement, provided, however, that any such surrender of an encumbered Undivided Interest may only be surrendered upon (i) the written consent of each Secured Party that holds a security interest in such Undivided Interest and a release of such Secured Partys security interest being provided by such Secured Party, and any required governmental approvals and (ii) receipt of any necessary governmental approvals; and (c) cure of all Events of Default then existing on the part of the Surrendering Party. The intent of the foregoing is that the remaining Co-Tenant shall own all undivided interests in the Shared Facilities. The surrender of its Undivided Interest shall not relieve the Surrendering Party of any of its obligations under this Agreement or any other agreement entered into pursuant to this Agreement, unless expressly provided for in this Agreement, or in a writing between the Parties. All reasonable costs and expenses, including reasonable attorneys' fees and expenses, incurred by the Shared Facilities Manager or remaining Co-Tenant in connection with the actual or proposed withdrawal of a Co-Tenant shall be paid or reimbursed by the withdrawing Co-Tenant upon any request therefor from the Shared Facilities Manager and the remaining Co-Tenant, as applicable. ARTICLE III TERM 8 Execution Version The term of this Agreement (the Term) will commence on the Effective Date, and shall continue in effect for the duration of the Crescent Ridge ISA and the Lone Tree Wind ISA. Notwithstanding the foregoing, the Agreement shall terminate, subject to obtaining any necessary prior FERC approvals for such termination, upon the first occurrence of one of the following: (i) a single Co-Tenant becoming the owner of the entire ownership interest in all of the Shared Premises and Facilities, or (ii) the mutual written agreement of all the Co-Tenants, with the consent of the then existing Secured Parties. ARTICLE IV INDEMNITY, USE AND COMPLIANCE 4.1 Cross Indemnity. (a) Each Co-Tenant (an Indemnifying Party) shall indemnify, defend and hold harmless the other Co-Tenant and its respective Affiliates (excluding the relevant indemnitor, as applicable) and all of its respective officers, directors, employees, agents, partners, shareholders and representatives (an Indemnified Party) from and against any and all losses, damages, liabilities, claims, judgments, liens, penalties, costs and expenses, including, without limitation, reasonable attorneys and consultants fees (collectively, Losses), which may be imposed upon or incurred by such Indemnified Party or asserted against such Indemnified Party by any third person or entity (a) (1) in connection with the Indemnifying Partys breach of this Agreement, (2) failure to comply in any material respect with applicable Law, or (3) any grossly negligent or willful acts or omissions of or on behalf of the Indemnifying Party on or with respect to such Co- Tenants Project Controlled Assets at any time after the Effective Date, except in each case to the extent caused by the Indemnified Partys gross negligence or willful misconduct, or (b) as a result of outages or curtailment of the Shared Facilities, other than in accordance with Section 5.5, proximately caused by the Indemnifying Party. (b) If for any reason whatsoever the Co-Tenants are or become jointly or jointly and severally liable to any third party for any obligation related to this Agreement and no Co- Tenant is required to indemnify the other Co-Tenants under Section 4.1(a), the respective liability of each of the Co-Tenants, as among themselves, will be limited severally to their respective Pro Rata Shares. Without limiting the foregoing, the liability of each Co-Tenant under this Section 4.1(b) will be in proportion to such Co-Tenant's respective Pro Rata Shares, and to the extent any indemnification obligations of the Co-Tenants under this Article 4 relate to any Project Controlled Assets, any Co-Tenant not owning any share of such Project Controlled Assets will not have any responsibility or liability for or with respect to any such indemnification obligations. Any Co- Tenant that may incur joint or joint and several liability to a third party in excess of such Co- Tenant's Pro Rata Share thereof as provided in this Section 4.1(b) shall be entitled to contribution and indemnity from the other Co-Tenant on a proportionate basis. 4.2 Indemnification of Shared Facilities Manager. Each Co-Tenant shall indemnify, defend, and hold harmless the Shared Facilities Manager and its Affiliates (excluding the relevant indemnitor, as applicable) and all of its respective officers, directors, employees, agents, partners, shareholders and representatives, from and against any and all Losses arising out of (i) the acts (or failures to act) of such Co-Tenant or 9 Execution Version its officers, directors, employees, agents, members and representatives, hereunder or (ii) subject to Section 4.3, the acts of the Shared Facilities Manager pursuant to its authority under this Agreement, provided the liability of each Co-Tenant under this subsection (ii) shall be in proportion to its Pro Rata Share of such liability; and the Shared Facilities Manager, its owners, officers, directors and employees shall not be liable to such Co-Tenant or any third party for any obligation, liability, or commitment incurred by or on behalf of such Co-Tenant in accordance with the provisions of this Agreement; provided, however, that the Shared Facilities Manager, its officers, directors and employees shall not be entitled to indemnification hereunder to the extent any action, claim, demand, cost or liability results from breach of this Agreement or from the Shared Facilities Managers gross negligence or willful misconduct. 4.3 Indemnification by the Shared Facilities Manager. The Shared Facilities Manager shall indemnify, defend and hold harmless each Co- Tenant and its Affiliates (excluding the relevant indemnitor, as applicable) and all of their respective officers, directors, employees, agents, partners, shareholders and representatives, from and against any and all Losses arising out of the Shared Facilities Managers gross negligence or willful misconduct. 4.4 Lapse in the Availability and Operation of the Shared Facilities The Co-Tenants acknowledge that in the event the Shared Facilities used to provide interconnection service become unavailable for any reason to carry energy produced by each Co- Tenant across the Point of Interconnection, each Co-Tenants right to utilize the Transmission Providers transmission system will be suspended for the duration of such unavailability, pursuant to Schedule F of the Crescent Ridge ISA and the Lone Tree Wind ISA. The Co-Tenants further acknowledge that in the event that either of the Co-Tenants ceases operations of the Shared Facilities, removes from service the Shared Facilities upon which each Co-Tenants interconnection service hereunder depends, or for any other reason the Shared Facilities become permanently unavailable to transmit energy produced by either Project, it shall be the Co-Tenants responsibility to acquire and install, or to obtain rights to utilize, other interconnection facilities necessary to enable the Co-Tenants to deliver energy produced by their respective Projects to the Point of Interconnection, pursuant to Schedule F of the Crescent Ridge ISA or the Lone Tree Wind ISA, as applicable. 4.5 Limitations on Liability; Waiver of Consequential Damages. Except to the extent arising out of acts or omissions constituting gross negligence, fraud, willful misconduct or breach of this Agreement by the Shared Facilities Manager, the maximum aggregate liability of Crescent Ridge in its role as the Shared Facilities Manager for Losses under this Agreement shall not exceed an amount equal to $180,000. In no event shall the liability of the Shared Facility Manager or a Co-Tenant under this Agreement, as applicable (other than liability arising out of acts or omissions constituting negligence, fraud, willful misconduct or breach of this Agreement by the Shared Facilities Manager or a Co-Tenant) exceed, in any calendar year during the Term, the amount of actual insurance recoveries. 10 Execution Version NOTWITHSTANDING ANYTHING TO THE CONTRARY IN THIS AGREEMENT, NEITHER OF THE PARTIES SHALL BE ENTITLED TO, AND EACH PARTY HEREBY WAIVES ANY AND ALL RIGHTS TO RECOVER CONSEQUENTIAL, INCIDENTAL AND PUNITIVE OR EXEMPLARY DAMAGES, HOWEVER ARISING, WHETHER IN CONTRACT, IN TORT OR OTHERWISE, UNDER OR WITH RESPECT TO ANY ACTION TAKEN IN CONNECTION WITH THIS AGREEMENT INCLUDING CLAIMS OF CUSTOMERS, COST OF MONEY, LOSS OF PROFIT, LOSS OF USE OF CAPITAL OR REVENUE, EXCEPT TO THE EXTENT SUCH DAMAGES ARE OTHERWISE PAYABLE AS EXPRESSLY SET FORTH HEREIN, INCLUDING UNDER SECTIONS 4.1 THROUGH 4.4 ABOVE. 4.6 Environmental Compliance. Without limiting the scope of each Co-Tenants obligations under Section 4.1, each Co-Tenant will, with respect to such Co-Tenants Project Controlled Assets, be responsible for all investigations, studies, clean up, corrective actions or responses or remedial actions required by any Governmental Authority now or hereafter authorized to regulate environmental or other matters or by any consent decree or court or administrative order now or hereafter applicable to such Co-Tenants use, operation or ownership of such Co-Tenants Project Controlled Assets. Each Co-Tenant will have the right (but not the obligation, unless otherwise required above) to participate in the management and control of all investigations and any environmental clean-up, remediation or related activities relating to such Co-Tenants Project Controlled Assets. 4.7 No Waste or Nuisance; Maintenance; No Interference. A Co-Tenant's use of the Shared Facilities and Premises or the operation of its Project may not interfere with the use and enjoyment by the other Co-Tenant of its respective rights in such Shared Facilities and Premises or the operation of its Project, except as specifically provided herein. Subject to the terms and conditions of this Agreement, each Co-Tenant hereby consents to the development and operation of the Projects, and each Co-Tenant shall cooperate in good faith to accommodate the other Co-Tenant's use of the Shared Facilities and Premises for the benefit of the Projects as contemplated by this Agreement (including, as appropriate, through the sharing of relevant technical information). No Co-Tenant will use or permit the use of the Shared Premises and Facilities in any manner that would violate applicable Laws, create waste or nuisance, or that would increase the rate or jeopardize the issuance or maintenance of any insurance policy relating to any or all of the Shared Premises and Facilities nor otherwise conduct or permit to be conducted operations on its Project Controlled Assets which would have similar effects on, or otherwise damage or interfere with, the Shared Facilities and Premises. 4.8 Liens. Except as provided in Section 8.2, no Co-Tenant will cause or permit any lien or encumbrance to be levied against or attached to the other Co-Tenants interests in the Shared Premises and Facilities. 4.9 Project Controlled Assets Taxes. Each Co-Tenant will pay all real and personal property taxes and assessments, 11 Execution Version general or special, levied against such Co-Tenants Project Controlled Assets. All such taxes and assessments will be paid before delinquency and before any fine, interest or penalty will become due or be imposed for their non-payment. 4.10 Insurance. Each Co-Tenant shall, at its expense, maintain (i) a commercial general liability insurance policy insuring it and the other Parties for bodily injury and property damage caused by such Partys use or operational management, as applicable, of the Shared Premises and Facilities, with a limit not less than One Million Dollars ($1,000,000) per occurrence, accident or incident and an aggregate limit per policy term of not less than Two Million Dollars ($2,000,000), and (ii) all risks property insurance, in an amount not less than the full replacement cost thereof, insuring such Co-Tenants Undivided Interest in the Shared Facilities; provided, however, that the Co- Tenants may instead (x) request that the Shared Facilities Manager place such property insurance coverage, in which case each Co-Tenant shall be named a loss payee and/or (y) jointly purchase such property insurance. All such policies of insurance (other than a policy purchased jointly) shall (a) name the other Co-Tenant and the Shared Facilities Manager as an additional insured or loss payee (as applicable) on a primary, non-contributing basis and (b) waive the insurers right of subrogation against the other Co-Tenant and the Shared Facilities Manager. Certificates of such insurance evidencing the coverages required by this Agreement shall be provided to the other Parties upon reasonable request. Each Co-Tenant shall have the right to use a qualified program of self-insurance to meet the insurance requirements, and may also provide any such insurance pursuant to one or more blanket insurance policies maintained by such Party or its Affiliates. Notwithstanding the requirements above, the Parties may agree in writing to maintain jointly a general liability insurance policy and/or policy of casualty insurance covering the Shared Premises and Facilities in the amounts specified above, with the costs of such jointly maintained policies allocated between the Co-Tenants in accordance with each Co-Tenants Pro Rata Share. 4.11 Reserved 4.12 Credit Support. Unless otherwise agreed upon by the Shared Facilities Manager in writing, each Co-Tenant shall maintain Approved Creditworthiness or provide and maintain, at its expense, Approved Credit Support. ARTICLE V OPERATIONS AND MANAGEMENT 5.1 Interconnection Agreement Requirements. During the Term of this Agreement, the Shared Facilities Manager shall be the single point of contact with the Transmission Provider and the Transmission Owner as to all issues affecting the Shared Facilities and Premises or for issues specifying the need for a single point of contact under all applicable Interconnection Service Agreements. All disputes between the Parties to this Agreement shall be resolved between the Parties as set forth in Article 7. 12 Execution Version Lone Tree Wind and Crescent Ridge as Co-Tenants shall permit the Shared Facilities Manager an opportunity to review and comment on, and approve (as to the use of Shared Facilities and the role of the Shared Facilities Manager) any amendments to Interconnection Service Agreements prior to finalization thereof. 5.2 Appointment, Removal and Replacement of Shared Facilities Manager. Crescent Ridge is hereby appointed as the Shared Facilities Manager. (a) The Shared Facilities Manager shall hold such position until (i) it resigns for convenience and without any liability to the Parties upon at least ninety (90) days prior written notice to the Parties, (ii) it is removed for convenience upon at least ninety (90) days written notice to the Shared Facilities Manager by the Co-Tenants, (iii) it is removed for cause in the event of any bad faith, gross negligence, recklessness or willful misconduct in connection with performance of its duties hereunder upon notice from the Lone Tree Wind, or (iv) Crescent Ridge ceases operation or desires to Transfer its interconnection rights to another party. (b) If the Shared Facilities Manager is removed for any of the reasons set forth in Section 5.2(a), then the other Co-Tenant, Lone Tree Wind, will either serve as Shared Facilities Manager or select a replacement that is experienced and qualified to perform the duties of the Shared Facilities Manager for similar facilities, as set forth herein. Lone Tree Wind shall notify Crescent Ridge in writing within fifteen (15) days of receipt of the written notice set forth in Section 5.2(a) if it plans to serve as Shared Facilities Manager or select a replacement.
